          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-box">
          <h4>Quality First</h4><p>
            Rigorous testing and code review processes ensure robust, secure,
            and maintainable solutions.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-box">
          <h4>Dedicated Support</h4><p>
            Long-term partnership with ongoing maintenance, updates, and
            technical support.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="faq-container">
        <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
          Common questions about our custom software development process in the
          UAE.
        </p>

        <div class="faq-list">
          <details>
            <summary>How long does it take to build custom software?</summary>
            <p>
              Timeline depends on scope and complexity. A focused internal tool
              or workflow automation system can typically be delivered within
              four to eight weeks. A full enterprise platform with multiple
              integrations, user roles, and reporting layers generally requires
              three to six months. After the discovery phase, we provide a
              detailed project roadmap with milestones and delivery dates.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary
              >How is custom software different from using an off-the-shelf
              product?</summary
            >
            <p>
              Off-the-shelf software is built for the widest possible market,
              which means it includes features you'll never use and lacks the
              specific functionality your business actually needs. Custom
              software is engineered around your workflows from day one,
              integrates with your existing systems, and can be extended without
              depending on a third-party vendor's product roadmap or pricing
              changes.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary
              >Can you integrate with our existing systems and legacy software?</summary
            >
            <p>
              Yes — this is one of the most common requirements we handle. Many
              projects involve connecting new custom software to existing
              databases, third-party platforms, or legacy systems that predate
              modern APIs. We build the middleware, data migration scripts, and
              integration layers needed to connect old and new infrastructure
              without disrupting ongoing operations.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary
              >Can you take over a project that another developer started?</summary
            >
            <p>
              Yes. We regularly onboard projects mid-development. We begin with
              a code and architecture audit to understand the current state,
              identify technical debt, and agree on a remediation plan before
              writing new code. The goal is always to stabilize first, then
              improve.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary
              >How do you handle data security and UAE regulatory compliance?</summary
            >
            <p>
              Security is incorporated throughout the development process, not
              bolted on at the end. We follow OWASP secure coding standards,
              implement role-based access controls, and design systems with UAE
              data residency requirements and the UAE Personal Data Protection
              Law (PDPL) in mind. For regulated industries, we can also support
              compliance with sector-specific standards.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>What happens after the software is launched?</summary>
            <p>
              We offer structured post-launch support and maintenance packages
              covering bug fixes, performance monitoring, security patches, and
              ongoing feature development. Most clients continue with us on a
              retainer basis, treating GeneralSoft as an extension of their
              internal technology team.
            </p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

